supply, at runtime (see README.md); nothing in the original data file is modified.

SABA (Super ACiD Block Attack)
------------------------------
In 2002 the authors re-released the same game, renamed SABA, to avoid confusion
with The Tetris Company's products. SABA is (C) 1997/2002 Jason Pimble & Scott
Emerle (same credits as above) and is distributed by them as freeware. Its data
file `saba.dat` is byte-identical to `ATET.DAT` except the title-screen logo, so
this port plays identically from either.

The pre-built RELEASE downloads (not the source repository) bundle SABA's intact,
unmodified original archive `saba.zip` exactly as the authors distribute it
(from dddgames.com), so the download is turnkey. That archive is redistributed
whole and unaltered, per its own freeware terms; the port itself remains
asset-free and simply reads `saba.dat` from the bundled archive at runtime. If you
prefer the original "ACiD Tetris" title screen, you can drop in ACiD Tetris's own
`ATET.DAT` instead (see README.md).

